[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory block is freed twice, causing the process to abort.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue overview  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  While running the fuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/out/[0m[95mapi[0m[39m -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, AddressSanitizer [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetected a double‐free in thread T0. The error occurs in the function [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` inside `fuzz/api.c` at line [0m[1;36m3580[0m[39m.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  This is a classic double‐free vulnerability, where a pointer to an allocated [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory region is freed more than once, leading to memory corruption and potential [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity exploitability.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The problematic pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m0x5020000000b0[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was originally allocated via [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlFuzzMalloc` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `fuzz/fuzz.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m through a call to `xmlStrndup`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`xmlStrdup` in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlstring.c`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The first free happens at `api.[0m[1;92mc:3580[0m[39m` within the fuzz harness’s test‐one‐input[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction. Immediately afterward, control returns to the same function and attempts [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto free the same pointer again.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The backtrace shows involvement of the XML comment creation function [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlNewComment` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `tree.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which uses `xmlStrdup`, tying the allocation–free [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpair into the API fuzzing code.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Areas for investigation  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `fuzz/api.c`, especially around line [0m[1;36m3580[0m[39m in `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`—the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry point where input is parsed and freed.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `fuzz/fuzz.c`’s `xmlFuzzMalloc` wrapper to understand how allocations are [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtracked.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `xmlstring.c` functions `xmlStrndup` and `xmlStrdup` to see how duplication [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand ownership are documented.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `tree.c`’s `xmlNewComment` to verify how comment nodes allocate and free their[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderlying string buffers.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo assumptions about root causes or fixes are made; this report strictly outlines [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhat was observed in the sanitizer output and which code paths should be reviewed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor a comprehensive understanding of the double‐free.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m260[0m[39m:    OP_XML_VALID_[0m[1;33mGET[0m[39m_VALID_ELEMENTS,[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz/api.[0m[1;92mc:1400[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1460[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1400[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35msetNode[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, node[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1401[0m[39m:                break;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1402[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1403[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1404[0m[39m:            case OP_XML_NEW_DOC_FRAGMENT: [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1405[0m[39m:                xmlNodePtr node;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1406[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1407[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mstartOp[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"xmlNewDocFragment"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1408[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mincNodeIdx[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1409[0m[39m:                node = [0m[1;35mxmlNewDocFragment[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mgetDoc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1410[0m[39m:                oomReport = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnode == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1411[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35msetNode[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, node[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1412[0m[39m:                break;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1413[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1414[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1415[0m[39m:            case OP_XML_CREATE_INT_SUBSET: [0m[1;39m{[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1416[0m[39m:                xmlDocPtr doc;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1417[0m[39m:                xmlDtdPtr dtd = NULL;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1418[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1419[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mstartOp[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"xmlCreateIntSubset"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1420[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mincNodeIdx[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1421[0m[39m:                doc = [0m[1;35mgetDoc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1422[0m[39m:                if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoc == NULL || doc->intSubset == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1423[0m[39m:                    dtd = [0m[1;35mxmlCreateIntSubset[0m[1;39m([0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1424[0m[39m:                        doc,[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1425[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;35mgetStr[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1426[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;35mgetStr[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1427[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;35mgetStr[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1428[0m[39m:                    oomReport = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdtd == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1429[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1430[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35msetNode[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlNodePtr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m dtd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1431[0m[39m:                break;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1432[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1433[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1434[0m[39m:            case OP_XML_NEW_DTD: [0m[1;39m{[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1435[0m[39m:                xmlDocPtr doc;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1436[0m[39m:                xmlDtdPtr dtd = NULL;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1437[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1438[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mstartOp[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"xmlNewDtd"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1439[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mincNodeIdx[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1440[0m[39m:                doc = [0m[1;35mgetDoc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1441[0m[39m:                if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoc == NULL || doc->extSubset == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1442[0m[39m:                    dtd = [0m[1;35mxmlNewDtd[0m[1;39m([0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1443[0m[39m:                        doc,[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1444[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;35mgetStr[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1445[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;35mgetStr[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1446[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;35mgetStr[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1447[0m[39m:                    oomReport = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdtd == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1448[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1449[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35msetNode[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlNodePtr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m dtd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1450[0m[39m:                break;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1451[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1452[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1453[0m[39m:            case OP_XML_COPY_DOC: [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1454[0m[39m:                xmlDocPtr copy;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1455[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1456[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mstartOp[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"xmlCopyDoc"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1457[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mincNodeIdx[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1458[0m[39m:                copy = [0m[1;35mxmlCopyDoc[0m[1;39m([0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1459[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;35mgetDoc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1460[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;35mgetInt[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root‐Cause Analysis  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Our AddressSanitizer log shows the double‐free involves a pointer allocated by [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlNewComment [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia xmlStrdup[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that is later freed twice:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. First, by the harness’s general string‐cleanup loop:  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < REG_MAX; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mvars->strings[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Second, when the harness tears down all nodes via [0m[1;35mdropNode[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlFreeNode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich frees each node’s content pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe buffer created by xmlNewComment[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Investigation of the harness operations reveals that certain API [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls—specifically the “raw‐string” getters [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. OP_XML_NODE_LIST_[0m[1;33mGET[0m[39m_RAW_STRING [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand/or OP_XML_STRING_[0m[1;33mGET[0m[39m_NODE_LIST[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m—are returning a pointer directly into a node’s [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternal content buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor comment, text, or CDATA nodes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and storing it in [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvars->strings[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.  Thus two different cleanup paths both free the same memory.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Fix Strategy Overview  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   We must ensure that any API designed to return a “raw” string from a node never [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturns a direct alias of the node’s internal buffer.  Instead it must always [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturn an independently allocated copy.  This guarantees:  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The harness’s [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mvars->strings[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will free only buffers it owns [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcopies[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • The node‐destructor path [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlFreeNode via dropNode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will free only the node’s [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mown content buffer.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   • No single buffer is freed twice.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   As mandated, we will not modify the fuzzer harness.  Instead we will patch the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibrary code in tree.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe XML node‐string APIs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Patch Steps  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Locate and edit xmlNodeGetRawString in tree.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand, if present, [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlNodeListGetRawString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Identify the cases where the function returns `cur->content` directly, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39me.g.:  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type == XML_TEXT_NODE || cur->type == XML_CDATA_SECTION_NODE || [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcur->type == XML_COMMENT_NODE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              return cur->content;  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Change that path to return a duplicate:  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return [0m[1;35mxmlStrdup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->content[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - For all other node types [0m[1;39m([0m[39melements, attributes, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, where the code calls[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlNodeGetContent or xmlNodeListGetString [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich already returns newly allocated [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, continue to return that result unmodified.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. If xmlNodeListGetRawString is a separate API in tree.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39mit may wrap [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlNodeGetRawString over a list of nodes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, ensure it too never hands back an alias:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - After assembling or retrieving the raw string, always return a copy.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If xmlNodeListGetRawString currently merges child‐text by concatenation or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby calling xmlNodeGetContent, leave that logic unchanged [0m[1;39m([0m[39msince it already [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocates[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  Otherwise, wrap the direct‐alias path in xmlStrdup.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Document ownership in the function’s comment header:  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Clearly state that the caller is responsible for freeing the returned [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlChar* via [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Ensure library test suites or paranoia code paths are updated accordingly. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By centralizing the fix in the library [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtree.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, we preserve existing harness [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe fuzzer code continues to call these APIs and free their results [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muniformly[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We avoid touching the harness, per policy, and protect against other clients [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwho may currently assume xmlNodeGetRawString returns a newly allocated buffer.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We do not alter any external dependencies or fuzzing flags.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We retain all existing functionality: clients still receive raw node content, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly difference is they get their own copy.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects and Mitigation  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Slight increase in memory allocation and copying when calling [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlNodeGetRawString on text, CDATA, or comment nodes.  In practice, these calls are[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheap string duplicates and are already expected cost in many XML‐processing [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscenarios.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No change in semantics for element nodes or attribute nodes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtheir API already[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated new buffers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No risk of missing a free, since we explicitly return a newly allocated buffer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min all code paths that previously returned an alias.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Verification  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuild the library and run the existing libxml2 test suite.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re‐run the “api” fuzz target under AddressSanitizer; verify that the [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdouble‐free is resolved and no new leaks or use‐after‐frees are introduced.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm via additional unit tests that xmlNodeGetRawString and [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlNodeListGetRawString consistently deliver allocated buffers [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., compare the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer address to node->content and ensure they differ[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe codebase exhibits a double-free crash when running the libfuzzer harness [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m against the `api` target in `libxml2`. The [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer log indicates that a block of memory is freed twice: once during [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling of a comment node and again in a later cleanup routine. [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn attempted patch modified `tree.c` by removing the body of `xmlChildElementCount`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand inserting two new functions—`xmlNodeGetRawString` and [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlNodeListGetRawString`—in its place. After applying this patch, the build fails [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith numerous “function definition is not allowed here” errors, indicating that the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnew functions were placed inside another function’s scope or that braces are [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatched.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer run [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`run_fuzzer api …`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggers AddressSanitizer in [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfile `api.c`, line [0m[1;36m3580[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, reporting a double-free of an [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m11[0m[39m-byte allocation.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace shows the same memory being freed twice within the same fuzzer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miteration: first in `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mhandling of comment nodes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and again [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduring cleanup [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlikely in `xmlFreeNodeList` or related routines[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The error summary and dedup tokens point to calls in `xmlNewComment`, [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlStrdup`, and the fuzzer loop.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch replaces the implementation of `xmlChildElementCount` with a new [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstandalone function `xmlNodeGetRawString`.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It also defines `xmlNodeListGetRawString` immediately after, but appears to [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minsert both definitions inside the existing function body rather than at file [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscope.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No matching closing brace was provided for `xmlChildElementCount`, so subsequent [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction definitions become nested illegally.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBuild Error Log  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The compiler reports “function definition is not allowed here” starting at [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tree.[0m[1;92mc:3453:76[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe start of `xmlNodeListGetRawString`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Similar errors repeat for every function declared after that point [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlLastElementChild`, `xmlPreviousElementSibling`, `xmlFreeNodeList`, [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlFreeNode`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, confirming that the new functions have broken the brace [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The build halts after over [0m[1;36m20[0m[39m such errors.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The structure and brace balance in `tree.c` around the `xmlChildElementCount` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction and the new `xmlNodeGetRawString`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`xmlNodeListGetRawString` insertions.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The intended placement of the new helper functions: they must be at file scope, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot inside another function.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The memory management routines [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`xmlNewComment`, `xmlFreeNodeList`, [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlFreeNode`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m involved in the double-free path to understand why the same [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer is freed twice.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The interaction between `xmlStrdup`, `xmlFuzzMalloc`, and node cleanup functions [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the fuzzing API to see where ownership of allocated content is confused.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3150[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3151[0m[39m: * Unlike xmlAddChild this function does not merge text nodes.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3152[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3153[0m[39m: * If @cur is an attribute node, it is inserted before attribute[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3154[0m[39m: * @next. If the attribute list contains an attribute with a name[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3155[0m[39m: * matching @cur, the old attribute is destroyed.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3156[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3157[0m[39m: * See the notes in xmlAddChild.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3158[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3159[0m[39m: * Returns @cur or a sibling if @cur was merged. Returns NULL[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3160[0m[39m: * if arguments are invalid or a memory allocation failed.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3161[0m[39m: *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3162[0m[39m:xmlNodePtr[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3164[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mnext == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnext->type == XML_NAMESPACE_DECL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ||[0m                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3175[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3176[0m[39m: * xmlAddSibling:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3177[0m[39m: * @node:  the target node[0m                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3180[0m[39m: * Unlinks @cur and inserts it as last sibling of @node.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3181[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3182[0m[39m: * If @cur is a text node, it may be merged with an adjacent text[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3183[0m[39m: * node and freed. In this case the text node containing the merged[0m            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3187[0m[39m: * list containing @node. If the attribute list contains an attribute[0m          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3189[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3190[0m[39m: * See the notes in xmlAddChild.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3191[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3192[0m[39m: * Returns @cur or a sibling if @cur was merged. Returns NULL[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3193[0m[39m: * if arguments are invalid or a memory allocation failed.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3194[0m[39m: *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3301[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3302[0m[39m: * Unlink @cur and append it to the children of @parent.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3303[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3304[0m[39m: * If @cur is a text node, it may be merged with an adjacent text[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3305[0m[39m: * node and freed. In this case the text node containing the merged[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3306[0m[39m: * content is returned.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3307[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3308[0m[39m: * If @cur is an attribute node, it is appended to the attributes of[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3309[0m[39m: * @parent. If the attribute list contains an attribute with a name[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3310[0m[39m: * matching @elem, the old attribute is destroyed.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3311[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3312[0m[39m: * General notes:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3313[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3314[0m[39m: * Move operations like xmlAddChild can cause element or attribute[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3315[0m[39m: * nodes to reference namespaces that aren't declared in one of[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3316[0m[39m: * their ancestors. This can lead to use-after-free errors if the[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3317[0m[39m: * elements containing the declarations are freed later, especially[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3318[0m[39m: * when moving nodes from one document to another. You should[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3319[0m[39m: * consider calling xmlReconciliateNs after a move operation to[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3320[0m[39m: * normalize namespaces. Another option is to call[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3321[0m[39m: * xmlDOMWrapAdoptNode with the target parent before moving a node.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3322[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3323[0m[39m: * For the most part, move operations don't check whether the[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3324[0m[39m: * resulting tree structure is valid. Users must make sure that[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3325[0m[39m: * parent nodes only receive children of valid types. Inserted[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3326[0m[39m: * child nodes must never be an ancestor of the parent node to[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3327[0m[39m: * avoid cycles in the tree structure. In general, only[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3328[0m[39m: * document, document fragments, elements and attributes[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3329[0m[39m: * should be used as parent nodes.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3330[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtree.[0m[1;92mc:3300[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m3360[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3300[0m[39m: * @cur:  the child node[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3301[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3302[0m[39m: * Unlink @cur and append it to the children of @parent.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3303[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3304[0m[39m: * If @cur is a text node, it may be merged with an adjacent text[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3305[0m[39m: * node and freed. In this case the text node containing the merged[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3306[0m[39m: * content is returned.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3307[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3308[0m[39m: * If @cur is an attribute node, it is appended to the attributes of[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3309[0m[39m: * @parent. If the attribute list contains an attribute with a name[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3310[0m[39m: * matching @elem, the old attribute is destroyed.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3311[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3312[0m[39m: * General notes:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3313[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3314[0m[39m: * Move operations like xmlAddChild can cause element or attribute[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3315[0m[39m: * nodes to reference namespaces that aren't declared in one of[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3316[0m[39m: * their ancestors. This can lead to use-after-free errors if the[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3317[0m[39m: * elements containing the declarations are freed later, especially[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3318[0m[39m: * when moving nodes from one document to another. You should[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3319[0m[39m: * consider calling xmlReconciliateNs after a move operation to[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3320[0m[39m: * normalize namespaces. Another option is to call[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3321[0m[39m: * xmlDOMWrapAdoptNode with the target parent before moving a node.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3322[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3323[0m[39m: * For the most part, move operations don't check whether the[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3324[0m[39m: * resulting tree structure is valid. Users must make sure that[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3325[0m[39m: * parent nodes only receive children of valid types. Inserted[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3326[0m[39m: * child nodes must never be an ancestor of the parent node to[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3327[0m[39m: * avoid cycles in the tree structure. In general, only[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3328[0m[39m: * document, document fragments, elements and attributes[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3329[0m[39m: * should be used as parent nodes.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3330[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3331[0m[39m: * When moving a node between documents and a memory allocation[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3332[0m[39m: * fails, the node's content will be corrupted and it will be[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3333[0m[39m: * unlinked. In this case, the node must be freed manually.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3334[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3335[0m[39m: * Moving DTDs between documents isn't supported.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3336[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3337[0m[39m: * Returns @elem or a sibling if @elem was merged. Returns NULL[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3338[0m[39m: * if arguments are invalid or a memory allocation failed.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3339[0m[39m: *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3340[0m[39m:xmlNodePtr[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3341[0m[39m:[0m[1;35mxmlAddChild[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlNodePtr parent, xmlNodePtr cur[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3347[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mNULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3348[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3349[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3350[0m[39m:     * If parent is a text node, call xmlTextAddContent. This[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3351[0m[39m:     * undocumented quirk should probably be removed.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3352[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3353[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparent->type == XML_TEXT_NODE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3354[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlTextAddContent[0m[1;39m([0m[39mparent, cur->content, [0m[1;36m-1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3355[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mNULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3356[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mxmlFreeNode[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3358[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3359[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3360[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur->type == XML_ATTRIBUTE_NODE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtree.[0m[1;92mc:3432[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m3460[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3432[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3433[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3434[0m[39m: * xmlFirstElementChild:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3435[0m[39m: * @parent: the parent node[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3436[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3437[0m[39m: * Find the first child node which is an element.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3438[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3449[0m[39m:    switch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparent->type[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3459[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3460[0m[39m:    while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur != NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz/api.[0m[1;92mc:3525[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m3540[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3525[0m[39m:                            prop->prev = copy;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3526[0m[39m:                        destParent->properties = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlAttrPtr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m copy;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3527[0m[39m:                    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcopy->type != XML_TEXT_NODE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3528[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;35mxmlAddChild[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdestParent, copy[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3530[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3531[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3532[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mxmlDOMWrapFreeCtxt[0m[1;39m([0m[39mctxt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3534[0m[39m:                break;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3535[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3536[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3537[0m[39m:            case OP_XML_CHILD_ELEMENT_COUNT:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3538[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mstartOp[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"xmlChildElementCount"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
