[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3540[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35msetInt[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mxmlChildElementCount[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mgetNode[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Restore xmlChildElementCount untouched and ensure its closing brace remains at [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfile scope:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Revert any modifications between the `unsigned long [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mxmlChildElementCount[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlNodePtr parent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` signature and its matching `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlines [0m[1;36m3407[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m3431[0m[39m in tree.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This fixes the “function definition is not allowed [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhere” compiler errors caused by missing or shifted braces.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Insert the two new helper functions at file scope immediately after the closing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbrace of xmlChildElementCount [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand before xmlFirstElementChild[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - xmlNodeGetRawString[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - xmlNodeListGetRawString[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Both functions must:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Accept the same parameters as their “raw” counterparts in the harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`const[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlDoc *doc, const xmlNode *cur, int inLine`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Call the existing xmlNodeListGetString [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich allocates its own buffer via [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlMalloc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to get a temporary string.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Duplicate that temporary buffer using xmlStrdup [0m[1;39m([0m[39mso ownership is transferred [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto the caller/fuzzer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Free the temporary buffer via xmlFree to avoid leaks.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. Return the newly duplicated string, which the harness will free exactly once.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed patch outline in tree.c:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   After the line:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   that closes xmlChildElementCount, insert:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * xmlNodeGetRawString:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * @doc: the document context[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * @cur: the node to extract content from[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * @inLine: whether to include in-line text[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m *[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * Returns a newly allocated xmlChar* which the caller [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfuzzer harness[0m[1;39m)[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * must free. Internally uses xmlNodeListGetString to assemble content,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * then duplicates it to avoid double-free of node->content.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlChar *[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mxmlNodeGetRawString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst xmlDoc *doc, const xmlNode *cur, int inLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    xmlChar *tmp, *ret;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return NULL;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* xmlNodeListGetString allocates a buffer via xmlMalloc *[0m[35m/[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    tmp = [0m[1;35mxmlNodeListGetString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoc, cur, inLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return NULL;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Duplicate for harness ownership *[0m[35m/[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ret = [0m[1;35mxmlStrdup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return ret;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * xmlNodeListGetRawString:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * @doc: the document context[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * @cur: the first node in the list[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * @inLine: whether to include in-line text[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m *[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * Similar to xmlNodeGetRawString but works on node lists.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * Returns a newly allocated xmlChar* for the caller to free.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlChar *[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mxmlNodeListGetRawString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst xmlDoc *doc, const xmlNode *cur, int inLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    xmlChar *tmp, *ret;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return NULL;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    tmp = [0m[1;35mxmlNodeListGetString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoc, cur, inLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return NULL;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ret = [0m[1;35mxmlStrdup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return ret;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By restoring xmlChildElementCount exactly, we fix the brace mismatch that [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcaused subsequent functions to be nested illegally.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Placing helpers at file scope ensures no more “function definition is not [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowed here” errors.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Wrapping xmlNodeListGetString in a duplication/frees sequence transfers [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mownership of a fresh buffer to the fuzzer harness. The harness’s [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mvars->strings[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` will free only the duplicated buffer, while the tree [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`xmlFreeNodeList` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `xmlFreeNode`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m continues to free each node’s internal [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`content` exactly once.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This eliminates the double-free: the harness no longer frees internal node [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffers, only the helper’s own copy.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Preservation of existing functionality:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes are made to the fuzzing harness or test code.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing tree traversal, dump, and cleanup logic remains untouched.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Memory ownership is made explicit only for the new “raw” retrieval APIs.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential side effects & mitigation:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Slight extra memory allocation for the helper wrappers; acceptable overhead in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing context.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No change to raw behavior of xmlNodeListGetString; only duplicated for safety.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No broad exception catching or library modifications; all at file scope in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtree.c.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Testing:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuild libxml2 with the patch and run the libfuzzer `api` target.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm no double-free ASAN errors and verify successful builds.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing unit and regression tests to ensure no regressions.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [33mCC[0m=[35m/work/ccache/[0m[95mclang[0m                                                                [2m               [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33mCXX[0m=[35m/work/ccache/[0m[95mclang++[0m                                                             [2m               [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33mCFLAGS[0m=-O1   -fno-omit-frame-pointer   -gline-tables-only                            [2m               [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         -Wno-[33merror[0m=[35mincompatible[0m-function-pointer-types   -Wno-[33merror[0m=[35mint[0m-conversion           [2m               [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         -Wno-[33merror[0m=[35mdeprecated[0m-declarations   -Wno-[33merror[0m=[35mimplicit[0m-function-declaration        [2m               [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         -Wno-[33merror[0m=[35mimplicit[0m-int   -Wno-[33merror[0m=[35mvla[0m-cxx-extension                               [2m               [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         -DFUZZING_BUILD_MODE_UNSAFE_FOR_PRODUCTION -[33mfsanitize[0m=[35maddress[0m                        [2m               [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         -fsanitize-address-use-after-scope -[33mfsanitize[0m=[35mfuzzer[0m-no-link                         [2m               [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33mCXXFLAGS[0m=-O1   -fno-omit-frame-pointer   -gline-tables-only                          [2m               [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         -Wno-[33merror[0m=[35menum[0m-constexpr-conversion                                                 [2m               [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         -Wno-[33merror[0m=[35mincompatible[0m-function-pointer-types   -Wno-[33merror[0m=[35mint[0m-conversion           [2m               [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer-detected double-free during fuzzing of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibxml2’s API [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, triggered when freeing memory allocated [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvia `xmlStrndup/xmlNewComment` and related calls. In response, a patch attempt was [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmade in `tree.c` to introduce two new helper functions—`xmlNodeGetRawString` and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlNodeListGetRawString`—that duplicate the output of `xmlNodeListGetString`, free[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe original, and return a safely malloc’d copy. After applying the patch, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation fails with a redefinition error for `xmlNodeListGetRawString` [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefined earlier in the file[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and warnings about dropping `const` qualifiers when [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalling `xmlNodeListGetString`. Consequently, the build is aborted and the issue [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains unresolved.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - During a libFuzzer run of the `api` target, AddressSanitizer reports a [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdouble-free at `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `api.[0m[1;92mc:3580[0m[39m`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The backtrace shows that memory is first allocated via `xmlFuzzMalloc` → [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlStrndup` [0m[1;39m([0m[39minside `xmlNewComment`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and later freed twice by `__interceptor_free`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min successive calls to `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run ends with `==ERROR: AddressSanitizer: attempting double-free`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the subprocess exits with status [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A patch was added to `tree.c` around line [0m[1;36m3398[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m3465[0m[39m.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch reformats the existing `xmlChildElementCount` function signature and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthen appends definitions for:  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `[0m[1;35mxmlNodeGetRawString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst xmlDoc *doc, const xmlNode *cur, int inLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `[0m[1;35mxmlNodeListGetRawString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst xmlDoc *doc, const xmlNode *cur, int inLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Each new function calls `xmlNodeListGetString`, checks for NULL, duplicates [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe result via `xmlStrdup`, frees the temporary buffer, and returns the duplicate.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Build Output After Patch  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compile error:  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     tree.[0m[1;92mc:3465:1[0m[39m: error: redefinition of ‘xmlNodeListGetRawString’  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     tree.[0m[1;92mc:1615:1[0m[39m: note: previous definition is here  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Warnings: passing `const xmlDoc *` to `[0m[1;35mxmlNodeListGetString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlDocPtr, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdiscards qualifiers.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Build aborts with `make[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m][0m[39m: *** [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mlibxml2_la-tree.lo[0m[1;39m][0m[39m Error [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The existing definition of `xmlNodeListGetRawString` at line [0m[1;36m1615[0m[39m in `tree.c`:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirm intended behavior and ownership semantics.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All uses of `xmlNodeListGetString` and corresponding `xmlFree` calls in the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAPI fuzz target [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`api.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, to trace where double frees occur.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Memory-management conventions around `xmlStrdup`, `xmlFree`, and [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlFuzzMalloc` in the fuzz harness and core library.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Potential const-correctness issues in caller signatures [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`const xmlDoc *`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vs.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcallee [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`xmlDocPtr`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlibxml2[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp7eyelbel[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce api[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue arose when running the libfuzzer harness against libxml2’s API [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode: AddressSanitizer reported a double-free in `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecifically freeing the same [0m[1;36m11[0m[39m-byte buffer twice. In response, a patch was [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroduced in `tree.c` to replace the direct return of [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlNodeListGetStringInternal` with a pair of calls—one to `xmlNodeListGetString` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand one to `xmlStrdup`—so that the returned string could be safely freed once. The [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch also added a new wrapper `xmlNodeGetRawString` and removed a duplicated [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefinition of `xmlFirstElementChild`. After applying the patch, the build broke: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe linker could not resolve `xmlFirstElementChild` when compiling `api.c`, leading[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto a linker error and aborting the build.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A fuzzing run [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`run_fuzzer api`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggered AddressSanitizer’s double-free [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetection:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Heap block at `[0m[1;36m0x5020000000b0[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize [0m[1;36m11[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was freed twice in the same [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall to `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - The first free happened in `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` at `api.[0m[1;92mc:3580[0m[39m`, and a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecond free occurred later in that function call path.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - The allocation path was traced back through `xmlFuzzMalloc` → `xmlStrndup` →[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlStrdup` → `xmlNewComment`, indicating the string returned from the internal API[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas being both duplicated and freed twice.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Key stack frames:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - free in `asan_malloc_linux.cpp`[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `fuzz/api.c`[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - `Fuzzer::ExecuteCallback` → `RunOneTest` → `FuzzerDriver` → `main`[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - File modified: `tree.c`[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Changes introduced:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a. In `xmlNodeListGetRawString`, replaced[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```c[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlNodeListGetStringInternal[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlDocPtr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m doc, list, escMode[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        with a two-step approach:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```c[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        tmp = [0m[1;35mxmlNodeListGetString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlDocPtr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m doc, list, escMode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mNULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ret = [0m[1;35mxmlStrdup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mret[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b. Added a new function `xmlNodeGetRawString` wrapping [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlNodeListGetRawString`.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     c. Removed the duplicate block of code defining `xmlFirstElementChild`.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Intention: ensure any buffer returned by the internal call is freed exactly [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monce and the caller owns its own duplicate.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Result of Applying Patch  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The build now fails at link time with:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     api.c:[0m[33m...[0m[39m undefined reference to `xmlFirstElementChild'[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     clang++: error: linker command failed with exit code [0m[1;36m1[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A DWARF warning [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`invalid or unhandled FORM value: [0m[1;36m0x25[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m also appears but the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritical error is the undefined symbol.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The removal of `xmlFirstElementChild` in `tree.c` orphaned references in [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`api.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe fuzz harness[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, causing the missing symbol.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Summary of build steps:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Docker image build succeeded.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - On compiling the fuzzers, the linker error occurs, aborting the build.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The definition and usage of `xmlFirstElementChild`:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Confirm whether it is declared in a header, how many callers exist [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnotably [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `api.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Decide if the function should be restored in `tree.c` or callers updated.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The memory-management functions involved in the double-free:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Verify all code paths in `xmlNodeListGetRawString` and [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlNodeGetRawString`.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Audit other APIs that return internal buffers for similar ownership issues. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The build system and headers:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Ensure that any new functions [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`xmlNodeGetRawString`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are properly declared [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min public headers if they are called externally.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Confirm consistency between declarations and definitions to avoid further [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlinker errors.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39minclude/libxml/tree.h:[0m[1;36m1080[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1085[0m                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1080[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m int inLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1081[0m[39m:XMLPUBFUN xmlChar *[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1082[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[39mxmlNodeListGetRawString [0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst xmlDoc *doc,[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1083[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m const xmlNode *list,[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1084[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m int inLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1085[0m[39m:XMLPUBFUN int[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtree.[0m[1;92mc:1617[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1624[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1617[0m[39m:    int escMode = inLine ? [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m : [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1618[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1619[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* backward compatibility *[0m[35m/[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1620[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlist == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1621[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mNULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1622[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1623[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mreturn[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mxmlNodeListGetStringInternal[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlDocPtr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m doc, list, escMode[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1624[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Restore the `xmlFirstElementChild` definition  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The last patch mistakenly removed the only definition of [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlFirstElementChild` from `tree.c`, orphaning all calls in `api.c`. Re-insert the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginal implementation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m3443[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m3465[0m[39m in the pre-patch `tree.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m immediately [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter the `xmlChildElementCount`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`xmlGetLastChild` block. This will resolve the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mundefined reference at link time without changing the fuzzer harness or tests.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Keep the `xmlNodeListGetRawString` memory‐ownership fix  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Retain the two-step allocation in `xmlNodeListGetRawString`:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       tmp = [0m[1;35mxmlNodeListGetString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlDocPtr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m doc, list, escMode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return NULL;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ret = [0m[1;35mxmlStrdup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return ret;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This change ensures callers receive a freshly allocated buffer and only free [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit once, thus eliminating the double-free observed under AddressSanitizer.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Expose the new wrapper `xmlNodeGetRawString` in the public API  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `tree.c`, keep the wrapper:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     XMLPUBFUN xmlChar *[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mxmlNodeGetRawString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst xmlDoc *doc, const xmlNode *cur, int inLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcur == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return NULL;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return [0m[1;35mxmlNodeListGetRawString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoc, cur, inLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `include/libxml/tree.h`, add its prototype immediately after [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlNodeListGetRawString`:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     XMLPUBFUN xmlChar *[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mxmlNodeGetRawString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mconst xmlDoc *doc,[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         const xmlNode *cur,[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         int inLine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Although the harness does not call this new function, exposing it prevents [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuture linkage issues if users adopt it.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Verify symbol exports [0m[1;39m([0m[39mversion script[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that `xmlFirstElementChild`, `xmlNodeListGetRawString`, and the new [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlNodeGetRawString` are marked for export in `libxml2.syms`. If [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlNodeGetRawString` is not yet listed under the `global:` section, append it [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malongside its peers so that downstream linkers can resolve it.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Sanity‐check existing declarations  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure `include/libxml/tree.h` contains the correct declarations for:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - xmlChildElementCount  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - xmlFirstElementChild  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - xmlLastElementChild  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - xmlNextElementSibling  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - xmlPreviousElementSibling  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - xmlNodeListGetRawString  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - xmlNodeGetRawString  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Rebuild and validate  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Reconfigure and rebuild the library.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run the libfuzzer `api` harness to confirm:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m No double-free is reported.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m No undefined‐reference linker errors occur.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m All existing tests, including those for child/element traversal and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mraw‐string extraction, pass unchanged.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Restoring `xmlFirstElementChild` directly addresses the undefined reference in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`api.c` without touching harness code.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keeping the two-step allocation in `xmlNodeListGetRawString` is essential to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfixing the double-free root cause.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Introducing `xmlNodeGetRawString` as a public API follows the pattern of other [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlNode*` methods, providing a clear, safe interface.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Updating the version script safeguards symbol visibility for both existing [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality and our new wrapper.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This patch preserves backwards compatibility, does not alter fuzzer or test [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic, and confines changes to `tree.c`, `tree.h`, and the symbol map.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Potential side effects are limited: restoring an existing function and publishing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma new wrapper should not alter any existing behavior except fixing the [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory‐management bug and the linker failure.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer-detected double-free in the libxml2 fuzz [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtarget [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`api.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The sanitizer log shows that a small region [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m11[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated via `xmlFuzzMalloc`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`xmlStrdup` and then freed twice in [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempt modifies `xmlNodeListGetRawString` in `tree.c` to call [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlNodeListGetString` into a temporary buffer, duplicate that buffer with [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlStrdup`, free the temporary, and return the new copy. It also adds a new [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlNodeGetRawString` wrapper in the header and source.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the fuzzer run still triggers the same double-free at the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame callsite [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`api.[0m[1;92mc:3580[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating the patch did not prevent the double-free.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`api`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m crashes under AddressSanitizer with a double-free:  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ERROR: AddressSanitizer: attempting double-free on [0m[1;36m0x5020000000b0[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[33m...[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[39m in LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput [0m[35m/src/libxml2/fuzz/[0m[95mapi.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m3580:9[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The offending pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m11[0m[39m-byte region[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was originally allocated in [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlFuzzMalloc` → `xmlStrndup` → `xmlStrdup`.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sanitizer stack shows one `[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at the same line in [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`, and another `[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` of the same address immediately [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafterward, so the second free triggers the error.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The harness is invoking libxml2 API functions on fuzz-generated inputs, and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe failure stems from core tree-handling code and the fuzz driver, not the harness[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mitself.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key observations from the initial log  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The double-free always happens at `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` line [0m[1;36m3580[0m[39m in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`api.c`.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The allocation trace originates in `xmlFuzzMalloc` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfuzz support[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlStrdup` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcore string utility[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The tree module’s `xmlNewComment` is on the allocation stack, indicating [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomment-related functions are involved.[0m                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch attempt details  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `tree.c` at function `xmlNodeListGetRawString` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m1615[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Remove direct call to `xmlNodeListGetStringInternal`.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
